The case.

30
00:01:41,267 --> 00:01:43,394
<i>Isaacson v. Vakarian Holdings, Inc.</i>

31
00:01:43,561 --> 00:01:46,981
We've been assembling binders
for months.

32
00:01:47,148 --> 00:01:50,693
I've been slammed with the Oscar pool,
in case you weren't paying attention.

33
00:01:50,860 --> 00:01:52,362
Right. Sorry. I'll try harder.

34
00:01:53,279 --> 00:01:56,407
So this guy, Isaacson,
he dies of a heart attack.

35
00:01:56,574 --> 00:02:00,078
And his family, they're our clients,
sort through his financials...

36
00:02:00,245 --> 00:02:02,497
...looking to track his assets.
Lo and behold...

37
00:02:02,664 --> 00:02:06,501
...they find some old shares
in this company he invested in...

38
00:02:06,668 --> 00:02:08,795
...like 20 years back.

39
00:02:08,962 --> 00:02:10,713
Family tracks down the CFO...

40
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:13,675
...looking to cash out,
but he tells them, mmm...

41
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:15,927
...that corporation's been dissolved.

42
00:02:16,219 --> 00:02:19,139
-Isaacson's shares are worthless, right?
-Whoa.

43
00:02:19,347 --> 00:02:20,765
But Chuck does some digging.

44
00:02:20,932 --> 00:02:24,352
Turns out, they formed a new corporation
that's virtually identical...

45
00:02:24,519 --> 00:02:27,605
...to the old corp Isaacson invested in.
It's the same officers...

46
00:02:27,772 --> 00:02:30,066
-...same structure, everything.
-Ah.

47
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:34,487
Right? So Chuck finds exemption 4
in <i>Leannais v. Cincinnati.</i>

48
00:02:34,696 --> 00:02:36,906
Okay, yeah, listen,
I appreciate the effort...

49
00:02:37,073 --> 00:02:40,618
-...but can you just "big picture" it for me?
-Shut up. I am.

50
00:02:41,077 --> 00:02:43,913
Chuck won a case
Howard thought was unwinnable...

51
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:48,126
...using only the power
of obscure case law. Heh, heh, heh.

52
00:02:48,293 --> 00:02:50,587
And that's good?

53
00:02:50,795 --> 00:02:52,505
Yeah, very.

54
00:02:53,673 --> 00:02:56,009
-Congratulations, Mr. McGill.
-Jimmy.

55
00:02:56,176 --> 00:02:58,052
-Chuck. Big day, huh?
-Yeah.

56
00:02:58,219 --> 00:03:00,180
-Thanks....
-Kim Wexler.

57
00:03:00,346 --> 00:03:04,726
-Of course. You're one of our students?
