66
00:03:23,161 --> 00:03:25,371
<i>-Garcia v. Coe Manufacturing.</i>
CHUCK: Mm-hm.

67
00:03:25,538 --> 00:03:29,459
Sounds like it was <i>Isaacson v. Chuck</i>
<i>Handing Him His Butt On A Platter,</i> huh?

68
00:03:29,626 --> 00:03:32,837
Well, yeah,
but Isaacson is our client.

69
00:03:33,004 --> 00:03:36,257
Oh, really? Okay.
Well, the other guys' butts, then.

70
00:03:36,466 --> 00:03:38,927
Yeah. Served on platters. Right.
Thanks, Jimmy.

71
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:43,806
HOWARD: Hail the conquering hero.
-Heh, heh. Thanks, Howard.

72
00:03:44,140 --> 00:03:48,728
I hate to interrupt, but there's
a Mr. Bushmills waiting in my office.

73
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:50,438
Kim. Jimmy.

74
00:03:54,192 --> 00:03:55,652
[INDISTINCT DIALOGUE]

75
00:03:57,445 --> 00:03:59,614
That'll be you soon.

76
00:04:00,198 --> 00:04:01,699
Yup.

77
00:04:02,575 --> 00:04:04,035
Okay.

78
00:04:04,202 --> 00:04:05,453
See you later, Jimmy.

79
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:07,247
See you.

80
00:04:16,756 --> 00:04:18,716
Ben. What you got for me?

81
00:04:18,883 --> 00:04:21,010
BEN:
There's your winner.

82
00:04:22,679 --> 00:04:26,933
Think Pacino's gonna "hooah" his way
to Oscar glory, huh?

