94
00:06:13,873 --> 00:06:14,957
Um....

95
00:06:15,124 --> 00:06:18,961
Viola, can you look up the relevant
case law here for me?

96
00:06:33,768 --> 00:06:35,228
I'm, uh....

97
00:06:36,396 --> 00:06:39,607
I think it is maybe...

98
00:06:40,691 --> 00:06:43,694
<i>...uh, U.S. v. United Foods.</i>

99
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:46,197
Yeah.

100
00:07:38,374 --> 00:07:40,376
[WHIRRING]

101
00:07:43,963 --> 00:07:45,590
KIM:
Morning.

102
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:49,844
Jimmy. Morning.

103
00:07:50,011 --> 00:07:51,304
Oh, good morning.

104
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:53,598
I just was making the OJ.

105
00:07:53,764 --> 00:07:55,224
I see that.

106
00:07:55,391 --> 00:07:56,434
[WHIRRING STOPS]

107
00:08:03,107 --> 00:08:04,901
I didn't hear you come to bed.

108
00:08:06,027 --> 00:08:08,571
I was up late justifying
a giant horse statue...

109
00:08:08,738 --> 00:08:11,616
-...to the Park City zoning commission.
-How big we talking?

110
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:15,661
"I'm definitely overcompensating
for some other shortcoming" big.

111
00:08:18,331 --> 00:08:19,916
Your hours pretty much set now?

112
00:08:20,082 --> 00:08:22,168
Yeah. Weekdays, 9 to 4.

113
00:08:22,335 --> 00:08:25,254
-The busy time.
-Oh, yeah?

114
00:08:25,796 --> 00:08:28,299
It's dead, Kim. It's deader than disco.

115
00:08:28,466 --> 00:08:29,634
Oh, sorry.

116
00:08:31,052 --> 00:08:34,555
Does that mean you were able to schedule
an appointment with the therapist?

117
00:08:39,268 --> 00:08:41,646
I decided not to go.

118
00:08:44,524 --> 00:08:45,650
Oh.

119
00:08:47,777 --> 00:08:49,153
Um....

120
00:08:50,029 --> 00:08:51,489
Okay.

121
00:08:52,949 --> 00:08:54,158
[SIGHS]

122
00:08:55,535 --> 00:08:58,371
I thought you'd already decided to go?

123
00:08:58,538 --> 00:09:00,373
I know. I did.

124
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:02,166
But then...

125
00:09:03,626 --> 00:09:07,421
...time went by
and I kind of calmed down...

126
00:09:07,588 --> 00:09:10,675
...and I realized it's just--
It's just not for me.

127
00:09:11,133 --> 00:09:12,176
Why not?

128
00:09:14,053 --> 00:09:15,888
It's just not.

129
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:20,977
I don't think that navel-gazing
is gonna get me where I need to be.

130
00:09:21,143 --> 00:09:24,188
-Yeah, but how do you know--?
-Unless I try?

131
00:09:24,522 --> 00:09:26,107
It just doesn't feel right.

132
00:09:26,274 --> 00:09:28,234
I need to be moving forward, you know?

133
00:09:28,401 --> 00:09:29,819
And now I got this job.

134
00:09:29,986 --> 00:09:33,030
And I'm kind of on a path...

135
00:09:33,197 --> 00:09:36,033
...and just wanna give this a try.

136
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,326
Is that okay?

137
00:09:38,536 --> 00:09:40,496
Sure.

138
00:09:41,330 --> 00:09:44,292
Yeah. Of course, Jimmy.

139
00:09:44,709 --> 00:09:47,795
Yeah, listen,
I know you wanted me to go.

140
00:09:47,962 --> 00:09:50,381
You have to do what's best for you.

141
00:09:54,719 --> 00:09:58,681
Oof. I should go open up. Um....

142
00:10:00,808 --> 00:10:02,518
Sushi tonight?

143
00:10:02,685 --> 00:10:04,770
Yeah, that sounds great.

144
00:10:12,862 --> 00:10:14,030
[DOOR CLOSES]

145
00:10:23,873 --> 00:10:27,293
MAN: Should be fine for Friday, I think?
WOMAN: Yeah, Friday works.

146
00:10:27,460 --> 00:10:28,961
RICH:
Kim.

147
00:10:29,754 --> 00:10:31,339
-Hello, Rich.
-So good to see you.

148
00:10:31,505 --> 00:10:33,883
You too. Thanks for seeing me
on such short notice.

149
00:10:34,050 --> 00:10:36,302
You kidding?
I've been wanting to thank you...

150
00:10:36,469 --> 00:10:39,513
...since you sent Billy Gatwood our way.
So shall we?

151
00:10:40,222 --> 00:10:43,100
-So how long you got with that thing?
-Three more weeks.

152
00:10:43,267 --> 00:10:45,436
Can I sign it? Do people still do that?

153
00:10:45,603 --> 00:10:46,812
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

154
00:10:46,979 --> 00:10:49,148
Please, have a seat. Have a seat.

155
00:10:49,774 --> 00:10:54,028
I won't lie, losing Billy Gatwood
definitely hurt.

156
00:10:54,195 --> 00:10:57,281
Well, if it makes you feel any better,
I think he misses you.

157
00:10:57,448 --> 00:10:59,700
As long as he's taken care of, I'm happy.

158
00:10:59,867 --> 00:11:03,329
Well, you made it easy for us.
We just continued what you started.

159
00:11:04,163 --> 00:11:06,832
So, um, how's James holding up?

160
00:11:07,249 --> 00:11:10,044
I didn't get to speak with him
at the funeral.

161
00:11:10,628 --> 00:11:13,506
-We're taking it one day at a time.
-Hm.

162
00:11:13,673 --> 00:11:16,342
Grief moves at its own pace.

163
00:11:16,509 --> 00:11:18,260
And it's different for everybody.

164
00:11:18,427 --> 00:11:21,097
So give him my best.

165
00:11:21,263 --> 00:11:22,306
Thank you.

166
00:11:22,473 --> 00:11:24,350
So, what can I do for you?

167
00:11:25,643 --> 00:11:28,104
-I have a question for you.
-Mm-hm.

168
00:11:28,270 --> 00:11:30,731
How's your banking division?

169
00:11:31,524 --> 00:11:35,319
Well, we have some banking work,
but I wouldn't say we have a division.

170
00:11:36,612 --> 00:11:38,531
Would you like one?

171
00:11:52,336 --> 00:11:56,340
MIKE: Well, it's a good long way
from the rest of your operation.

172
00:11:56,507 --> 00:11:59,135
GUS:
It must remain completely separate.

173
00:12:00,010 --> 00:12:01,887
MIKE:
Two bedrooms each.

174
00:12:02,638 --> 00:12:04,557
Werner will probably take his own.

175
00:12:04,724 --> 00:12:07,143
The rest of the guys can double up.

176
00:12:07,643 --> 00:12:10,730
-Wired and plumbed?
-Yes.

177
00:12:10,938 --> 00:12:13,357
This is a good start.

178
00:12:14,150 --> 00:12:16,402
What do you have in mind?

179
00:12:16,569 --> 00:12:18,070
MIKE:
Hm.

180
00:12:20,865 --> 00:12:22,825
Couple treadmills over there.

181
00:12:22,992 --> 00:12:25,161
Barbells, weight bench.

182
00:12:25,327 --> 00:12:30,082
You build out a stocked bar, beer on tap.
I mean, they're German, so....

183
00:12:30,249 --> 00:12:31,667
Entertainment system here.

184
00:12:32,209 --> 00:12:36,172
DVD player, projector and screen set up
might be nice.

185
00:12:36,630 --> 00:12:38,591
A few La-Z-Boys or couches.

186
00:12:38,758 --> 00:12:40,885
Pool table, I don't know, foosball?

187
00:12:41,051 --> 00:12:44,680
Hell, we could even put up a hoop.
Germans play basketball, yeah?

188
00:12:44,847 --> 00:12:46,766
GUS:
I believe so.

189
00:12:47,308 --> 00:12:50,227
Werner said that this was gonna take
six months...

190
00:12:50,394 --> 00:12:54,190
...which means eight, at least,
probably 10, in total isolation.

191
00:12:54,356 --> 00:12:58,277
These guys are gonna be doing
10 hours heavy labor every day.

192
00:12:58,444 --> 00:13:02,406
Or night. Then coming home to this.
We can't just keep them alive...

193
00:13:02,573 --> 00:13:05,534
...we gotta keep them
from climbing the walls.

194
00:13:10,831 --> 00:13:12,750
Make a list.

195
00:13:15,377 --> 00:13:17,338
Security.

196
00:13:18,297 --> 00:13:22,510
I'd like a full-camera perimeter inside.
We'll keep it low profile.

197
00:13:22,676 --> 00:13:26,430
They'll know we'll be watching, we just
don't need to stick it in their faces.

198
00:13:26,597 --> 00:13:28,432
Outside too, obviously...

199
00:13:28,599 --> 00:13:32,812
...in case someone tries to find
a way in or out.

200
00:13:36,565 --> 00:13:38,776
I'll put a sally port on that door.

201
00:13:39,401 --> 00:13:41,862
We'll control it from the outside.

202
00:13:42,029 --> 00:13:45,825
And we're gonna need a trailer
to monitor the cameras.

203
00:13:45,991 --> 00:13:47,868
Close by...

204
00:13:48,035 --> 00:13:50,246
...two guys, 24-hour monitoring.

205
00:13:50,412 --> 00:13:52,373
Work in shifts.

206
00:13:52,540 --> 00:13:55,835
Let's say five guys, minimum.

207
00:13:56,168 --> 00:13:58,796
Probably help to have
a couple German speakers as well.

208
00:13:58,963 --> 00:14:00,631
I can provide you men.

209
00:14:00,798 --> 00:14:02,800
I'm gonna need to vet them. No offense.

210
00:14:02,967 --> 00:14:04,134
Of course.

211
00:14:09,181 --> 00:14:12,101
-What is it?
-Infection. Bad one.

212
00:14:14,895 --> 00:14:16,522
GUS:
I must leave.

213
00:14:16,689 --> 00:14:18,315
Tell Tyrus what you need.

214
00:14:18,482 --> 00:14:19,483
It will be done.

215
00:14:24,947 --> 00:14:26,907
You got a pen?

216
00:14:27,324 --> 00:14:30,160
-I'll remember.
-Yeah?

217
00:14:30,452 --> 00:14:33,372
Treadmills. You wanna check
wholesale providers...

218
00:14:33,539 --> 00:14:37,167
...these guys are gonna tear
right through consumer-grade.

219
00:14:40,462 --> 00:14:43,883
JIMMY:
I'd love to see what something, say, like...

220
00:14:44,049 --> 00:14:46,635
...a 24-footer would run me?

221
00:14:46,802 --> 00:14:49,013
WOMAN [ON PHONE]:
<i>Sorry, we just don't make them that big.</i>

222
00:14:49,179 --> 00:14:52,683
-Who does?
<i>-I can't think of anyone around here.</i>

223
00:14:52,850 --> 00:14:56,020
Well, who makes those
huge signs that the casinos have?

224
00:14:56,186 --> 00:14:57,313
[CELL PHONE BUZZING]

225
00:14:57,479 --> 00:15:00,399
You know what, never mind.
Thank you very much.

226
00:15:04,236 --> 00:15:05,529
Jimmy McGill.

227
00:15:05,696 --> 00:15:08,032
MAN:
<i>Yes. I'm looking for Jimmy McGill.</i>

228
00:15:08,198 --> 00:15:09,867
